The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 12 December is 10,324 (1,194.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 07 December, there were 654 new confirmed cases (75.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 491 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 33% (163 extra cases).
